{
  "texts": [
    "We used spherical-deconvolution informed filtering to assign a weight to each generated streamline and assess their contribution to the initial diffusion image 82.",
    "Finally, a healthy structural connectivity matrix was constructed by counting the number of weighted streamlines between each pair of regions of interest as delineated by the third version of the Automated Anatomical Label atlas 83.",
    "Next, to consider fiber bundles that originate and traverse lesioned tissue, a recent method for reconstruction was used only in the segmented lesion 17.",
    "The coined Single-Shell-3-Tissue Constrained Spherical Deconvolution (SS3T) algorithm uses only one diffusion shell and the unweighted b = 0 volumes.",
    "We used the shell with the highest gradient strength (i.e., b = 2800 s/mm 2) as it offered the best white-matter contrast 15, 80."
  ]
}